.NET Framework 3.5.name: RTConsole
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The main class to access the console system.

methods.name: AddCommandsInternal(Type[] types)
Execute(string command)
methods.summary: Analyze, parse, fire events and call the method associated with the command parameter.

events.name: CommandReceived
events.summary: Fired when a command is received (not analyzed, parsed or executed yet).

events.name: Exception
events.summary: Fired when a command throws an exception if HandleExceptions is enabled.

properties.name: EnableBuiltInCommands
properties.summary: Set to false to disable built in commands.

properties.name: EnableInternalLogs
properties.summary: Set to false to disable logs created by the console system.

properties.name: ExceptionFormatter
properties.summary: A formatter for exceptions thrown by the commands.

properties.name: HandleExceptions
properties.summary: Set to true to handle exceptions thrown by commands.

properties.name: Instance
properties.summary: A singleton to access the console system.

properties.name: Parser
properties.summary: The parser which converts the parameters resulted by the AbstractAnalyzer to instance of objects.

properties.name: SyntaxAnalyzer
properties.summary: The syntax analyzer which is used to validate and separate a command from its parameters.

properties.name: TypeConverters
properties.summary: The type converters to be used by the AbstractParser.

properties.name: Types
properties.summary: The types which to extract the commands from.
